
To run RE simulation on local system "input.PILOT" dictionary in your /src/radical/repex/config/input.json file should be modified as follows:
  - change "resource" value to localhost system, options are:
      - localhost.linux.x86 - 32 bit linux
      - localhost.linux.x86.64 - 64 bit linux
      - localhost.macos.x86 - 32 bit mac
      - localhost.macos.x86.64 - 64 bit mac
  - change "username" value to the one you are using on your laptop, e.g.: "username" : "<your_username>"
  - change "sandbox" value to directory of your chosen working directory on your laptop e.g.: "sandbox" : "<your_chosen_home_dir>"
###########################################################################################################
Example:

{
    "input.PILOT": {
        "resource": "localhost.linux.x86",
        "sandbox" : "/home/antons/SINON-WORK/abstract/ReplicaExchange/src/radical/repex",
        "username" : "antons",
        "runtime" : "20",
        "cleanup" : "False",
        "cores" : "4",
        "number_of_cycles": "3"
    }
}
