To run module on Stampede you need to perform three changes in /src/radical/repex/config/input.json file:
  - change "resource" value to "stampede.tacc.utexas.edu", e.g.: "resource": "stampede.tacc.utexas.edu"
  - change "username" value to the one assigned to you on Stampede, e.g.: "username" : "<your_username>"
  - change "cores" to 32, e.g.: "cores" : "32"

If you want to explicitly specify remote working directory you can do so by specifying "sandbox" value. 
###########################################################################################################
Example:

{
    "input.PILOT": {
        "resource": "stampede.tacc.utexas.edu",
        "username" : "antontre",
        "runtime" : "20",
        "cleanup" : "False",
        "cores" : "32",
        "number_of_cycles": "3"
    }
}
